# Part 1 – Feature Matrix Import and Metadata Alignment

## Import MZmine Feature Tables

```r
feat_neg <- read_csv("featurelist_neg.csv") %>%
  clean_names()

feat_pos <- read_csv("featurelist_pos.csv") %>%
  clean_names()
```

---

## Extract Feature Information

```r
feature_neg_info <- feat_neg %>%
  select(id, mz, rt, height)

feature_pos_info <- feat_pos %>%
  select(id, mz, rt, height)
```

These tables preserve feature metadata throughout filtering and statistical analysis.

---

## Extract Abundance Matrices

Peak area is used as the abundance metric.

```r
mat_raw_neg <- feat_neg %>%
  select(ends_with("_area"))

mat_raw_pos <- feat_pos %>%
  select(ends_with("_area"))
```

---

## Harmonize Sample Names

Convert MZmine-exported filenames into metadata-compatible filenames.

```r
colnames(mat_raw_neg) <- colnames(mat_raw_neg) %>%
  gsub("^datafile_", "", .) %>%
  gsub("_mz_ml_area$", ".mzML", .) %>%
  tolower()

colnames(mat_raw_pos) <- colnames(mat_raw_pos) %>%
  gsub("^datafile_", "", .) %>%
  gsub("_mz_ml_area$", ".mzML", .) %>%
  tolower()
```

---

## Import Metadata

```r
meta_neg <- read_excel(
  "metadata_batch1.xlsx",
  sheet = "neg"
) %>%
  clean_names() %>%
  mutate(filename = tolower(filename))

meta_pos <- read_excel(
  "metadata_batch1.xlsx",
  sheet = "pos"
) %>%
  clean_names() %>%
  mutate(filename = tolower(filename))
```

---

## Check Matrix–Metadata Consistency

```r
setdiff(colnames(mat_raw_neg), meta_neg$filename)
setdiff(meta_neg$filename, colnames(mat_raw_neg))

setdiff(colnames(mat_raw_pos), meta_pos$filename)
setdiff(meta_pos$filename, colnames(mat_raw_pos))
```

Expected output:

```r
character(0)
```

---

## Remove Metadata Entries Not Present in the Matrix

```r
meta_neg <- meta_neg %>%
  filter(filename %in% colnames(mat_raw_neg))

meta_pos <- meta_pos %>%
  filter(filename %in% colnames(mat_raw_pos))
```

---

## Reorder Matrices

```r
mat_raw_neg <- mat_raw_neg[
  ,
  meta_neg$filename,
  drop = FALSE
]

mat_raw_pos <- mat_raw_pos[
  ,
  meta_pos$filename,
  drop = FALSE
]
```

---

## Validate Alignment

```r
stopifnot(
  all(colnames(mat_raw_neg) == meta_neg$filename)
)

stopifnot(
  all(colnames(mat_raw_pos) == meta_pos$filename)
)
```

---

# Part 2 – Technical Replicate Collapsing (Positive Mode)

Some positive-mode datasets may contain technical replicate injections.

Biological samples are collapsed using the mean intensity across replicates, while blanks and QCs are retained individually.

```r
meta_pos <- meta_pos %>%
  mutate(
    collapse_id = if_else(
      sample_type == "sample",
      sample_id,
      filename
    )
  )
```

Replicates are averaged at the feature level.

The resulting objects are:

```text
mat_raw_pos_collapsed
meta_pos_collapsed
```

